<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="e30fe98f-32b8-57b1-8b1c-8406bfb15c50" activityNameId="ba49c211-7291-4f95-834c-3e8ae50833b7" parentActivityId="70d49a14-0faa-5c1d-b5ce-7e13b3d958a1" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">ethanolamine production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">141-43-5</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">2-Hydroxyethylamine</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Ethanolamine</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Monoethanolamine</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Aminoethanol</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">2-aminoethanol</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of monoethanolamine, diethanolamine and triethanolamine. The raw materials and chemicals used for production are included, as well as estimated emissions to air and water from production (incomplete) and estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant (approximation). Solid wastes are omitted.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a multi-output process that delivers the co-products monoethanolamine, diethanolamine and triethanolamine in variable quantities. These three substances are derivatives of ammonia. While the first and the last one are viscous, colourless, clear liquids at normal room temperature, diethanolamine is a crystalline solid. Ethanolamines are used as intermediates in the production of surfactants, as corrosion inhibitors, for gas purification, as intermediates for the production of various chemicals, and as cement additives. This dataset models the production of ethanolamines by the reaction of ethylene oxide with ammonia.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The inventory is based on stoichiometric calculations and estimations. The energy and water consumptions are approximated based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>combined production</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Production from ethylene oxide and ammonia with a process yield of 95%. The inventory is based on stoechiometric calculations. The emissions to air (0.2 wt% of raw material input) and water were estimated using mass balance. The treatment of the waste water in an internal waste water treatment plant is assumed (elimination efficiency of 90% for C).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Electricity is needed to run the process auxiliaries and the wastewater treatment. Fossil fuel is needed to generate the desired heat within the process scheme.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Date of published literature. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="daa6990e-7cfc-5859-b87d-860f5ea9722b" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="amount_monoethanolamine" casNumber="141-43-5" amount="1.0" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="RP1_PV/(RP1_PV + RP2_PV + RP3_PV)" intermediateExchangeId="ee245ab5-9f8d-4fe3-a739-ec656bbf9118" productionVolumeAmount="552500000.0" productionVolumeVariableName="RP1_PV" productionVolumeMathematicalRelation="0.5*1.7E+9">
