        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Worldwide capacity for ethanolamines was 1.7 million metric tonnes (3.7 billion pounds) in 2007 (Dow Safety Assessments for mono, di and triethanolamine. Accessed from http://www.dow.com/productsafety/finder/index.htm#P).
About half of the world production is monoethanolamine, 30 to 35% is diethanolamine and the remaining 15 to 20% triethanolamine (http://monographs.iarc.fr/ENG/Monographs/vol77/mono77-14.pdf).</productionVolumeComment>
