      <elementaryExchange id="63fbfcae-5f19-5fb6-a48d-016d719cbcd5" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000124-38-9" amount="0.0655900795798021" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="((amount_ethylene_oxide*(1 - process_efficiency) - EO_emissions_air)*0.9)*amount_ethylene_oxide_C_content_fossil*44/12" elementaryExchangeId="f9749677-9c9f-4678-ab55-c607dfdc2cb9" formula="CO2">
        <name xml:lang="en">Carbon dioxide, fossil</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The unreacted ethylene oxide was assumed to leave the production process with the wastewater. This amount was calculated taken into account losses of 0.2% raw material as air emissions, and the efficiency of the reaction (95%). Further it was assumed that this wastewater is treated in an internal wastewater plant. Therefore, a removal efficiency of 90% for ethylene oxide was assumed. The carbon contained in the removed ethylene oxide was accounted as CO2 emissions to air.</comment>
