      <elementaryExchange id="68c8cd59-f6c9-57b8-9495-dcd6112e1e9d" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="014798-03-9" amount="0.004476100210581465" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="(amount_ammonia*(1 - process_efficiency) - ammonia_emissions_air)*0.3*18.038/17.03" elementaryExchangeId="13331e67-6006-48c4-bdb4-340c12010036" formula="H4N+">
        <name xml:lang="en">Ammonium</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">With an efficiency of 95%, 5% of ammonia is found in the wastewater, except for the amount in air emissions. For the ammonia within the wastewater a removal efficiency for NH4-N of 70% and for total N of 50% was assumed. The remaining emissions to water were considered as ammonium (NH4) and nitrate (NO3). The nitrogen emitted to air (N2) and remaining in the sewage sludge was neglected.
MW of ammonia: 17.03 g/mol
MW ammonium: 18.038 g/mol</comment>
        <uncertainty>
